modules.description: Provides pretty-printers for error and write error types, and implements read, write, writev, and close operations on network flows. Operates on buffer types representing raw data and flow types representing network connections. Used to handle data transmission, error reporting, and connection termination in asynchronous network applications.

Provides functions for reading from and writing to buffered channels, including reading bytes, writing buffers, and flushing data. Works with byte sequences and channel objects that wrap unbuffered flow implementations. Used to manage data transmission in network applications with controlled flow control and buffering.

Provides functions to read from and write to network flows with buffering, including reading characters, lines, and exact byte counts, as well as writing strings, buffers, and lines. Operates on flow objects and buffer structures represented as Cstruct.t, with error handling for read and write operations. Used to manage reliable data transmission over network connections in asynchronous I/O contexts.
